main event: On 16 Jul 62, three witnesses observed a round, silvery object at Camp Carvel, Dunbar, Pa.
interesting points: The object traveled very low on the horizon at approximately 1 degree above, The sighting lasted about 5 minutes, The witnesses consisted of 1 male and 2 females, The object's course was easterly, Witnesses described the object as probably a balloon or aircraft based on conclusions.
